{"lemma":"شَعِيبَةٍ","slug":"شَعِيبَةٍ","root":"ش.ع.ب","root_slug":"ش-ع-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ع-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَعِيب","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22437"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Shuaib, a prophet of Islam who prophesied to the Midianites, sometimes identified with Jethro in the Bible"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Diminutive of شعب."},"ipa":["/ʃu.ʕajb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22437","headword_ar":"شَعِيبٌ","root":"$Eb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (A'Obeyd, S, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAwiyapN","text_ar":"رَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTiyHapN","text_ar":"سَطِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A'Obeyd, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has been repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieced:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is made of two hides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is made of two hides facing each other, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiy^aAm","text_ar":"فِيَام"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at their corners;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fy^Am","text_ar":"فيام"},{"kind":"text","text":"in [the making of]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAyid","text_ar":"مَزَايِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the taking of the hide and folding it, and then adding at the sides what will widen it: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is pieced"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tufoA^amu","text_ar":"تُفْاَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a third skin, between the two skins, that it may be rendered wider:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is made of two pieces joined together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that is sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoruwzap","text_ar":"مَخْرُوزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", K and TA, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHozuwzap","text_ar":"مَحْزُوزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on both sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) called thus because one part is joined to another: (L, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEubN","text_ar":"شُعُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old, worn-out skin for water or milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) because it is pieced, or repaired: (TA:) pl. as above. (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel's saddle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHolN","text_ar":"رَحْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": because it is joined, part to part: so in the saying of El-Marrár, describing a she-camel,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA hiYa xar~ato xar~a mino Eano yamiynihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        $aEiybN bihi A_iHomaAmuhaA waluguwbuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When she falls down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell down, there falls down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell down, from her right side a saddle by reason of which was her fevered and jaded state"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $aEiybN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شَعِيبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is a stranger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (AA, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariybN","text_ar":"غَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}